article.description: — Anthony Roberts' 20 points helped Purdue Fort Wayne defeat Oakland 98-77 on Saturday.
article.headline: Roberts scores 20, Purdue Fort Wayne takes down Oakland 98-77
article.linkText: Roberts scores 20, Purdue Fort Wayne takes down Oakland 98-77
article.story: AUBURN HILLS, Mich. -- — Anthony Roberts' 20 points helped Purdue Fort Wayne defeat Oakland 98-77 on Saturday. Roberts went 8 of 10 from the field for the Mastodons (8-1). Jalen Jackson added 17 points while going 7 of 7 and 3 of 4 from the free throw line, and they also had five rebounds and five assists. Quinton Morton-Robertson shot 6 for 10, including 5 for 8 from beyond the arc to finish with 17 points. D.Q. Cole led the way for the Golden Grizzlies (5-4) with 21 points, seven rebounds and four assists. Trey Townsend added 13 points and four assists for Oakland. Chris Conway also had 13 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
